      <abstract>
        <p>Memorial service for Pulitzer Prize-winning war reporter and author David Halberstam is scheduled for June 12 at Riverside Church in Manhattan; Halberstam died April 23 at age 73 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A memorial service for the Pulitzer Prize-winning war reporter and author David Halberstam is scheduled for 4 p.m. on Tuesday at Riverside Church, 490 Riverside Drive, in Manhattan. Mr. Halberstam died on April 23 at the age of 73.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A memorial service for the Pulitzer Prize-winning war reporter and author David Halberstam is scheduled for 4 p.m. on Tuesday at Riverside Church, 490 Riverside Drive, in Manhattan. Mr. Halberstam died on April 23 at the age of 73.</p>
        <p>The service, which is open to the public, is to include speeches by the journalists Dexter Filkins, Gay Talese and Anna Quindlen and a performance by Peter Yarrow of the group Peter, Paul and Mary.</p>
      </block>
